lender.occupational_info:
Exotic birds and parrots are highly intelligent creatures that can live more than 50 years when cared for properly. Sadly there are many people who do not understand the complexities of caring for these beautiful animals and become overwhelmed causing them to be sold, given away, set free or abused and neglected.
Montana's Parrot & Exotic Bird Sanctuary is the only active organization of it's kind in Montana, Wyoming, and Idaho, that understands the challenges facing these remarkable birds. The difficulty of finding resources for parrot and exotic bird owners is overwhelming. Education, appropriate supply sources and assistance are needed to ensure the proper care and support of these birds by their owners, and Montana's Parrot & Exotic Bird Sanctuary wants to continue to be that resource. We want to ensure that all parrots and exotic birds are well cared for and in loving, forever homes for the duration of their life time. With your help it can continue to be that way.
Montana's Parrot & Exotic Bird Sanctuary is dedicated to ensuring that all parrots and exotic birds are loved, appreciated and well cared for. Through the relinquishment and rehabilitation of unwanted birds, foster homes, adoption and education, Montana's Parrot & Exotic Bird Sanctuary works tirelessly with exotic bird owners and the public to create the optimum environment for these extraordinary pets to live full, happy, and healthy lives. Montana's Parrot & Exotic Bird Sanctuary has loved and supported more than 500 birds since taking in their first rescue in 2004 and continue to make a difference in the lives of these birds and their families today.
